<item>
            <title>[SOLR-628] make forceElevation a run time option in QueryElevationComponent</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-628</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;didn&apos;t get any reply to this in email, filing as bug to make sure it&apos;s dealt with before 1.3 release (either by fixing documentation, or by fixing bug &amp;#8211; still not sure what the problem is)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Date: Fri, 13 Jun 2008 11:41:26 -0700 (PDT)&lt;br/&gt;
From: Chris Hostetter&lt;br/&gt;
To: solr-user&lt;br/&gt;
Subject: QueryElevationComponent and forceElevation=true ?&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t know much about QueryElevationComponent but perusing the wiki docs and trying&lt;br/&gt;
it out with teh example configs i noticed that this URL didn&apos;t produce the output i&lt;br/&gt;
expected...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://localhost:8983/solr/elevate?q=ipod&amp;amp;fl=id,price&amp;amp;sort=price+asc&amp;amp;forceElevation=true&amp;amp;enableElevation=true&amp;amp;debugQuery=true&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://localhost:8983/solr/elevate?q=ipod&amp;amp;fl=id,price&amp;amp;sort=price+asc&amp;amp;forceElevation=true&amp;amp;enableElevation=true&amp;amp;debugQuery=true&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;..as far as i can tell, the forceElevation=true should cause &quot;MA147LL/A&quot; to always&lt;br/&gt;
apear at the top, regardless of the sort &amp;#8211; but that doesn&apos;t seem to be the case.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Am I reading the docs wrong, or is this a bug?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;</description>
