                            <comment id="12613743" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Tue, 15 Jul 2008 22:30:46 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I just checked the code, and forceElevation is a config-time option only.&lt;br/&gt;
The docs on the wiki seem to reflect this (forceElevation is only in the config section and not the usage section)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12613745" author="hossman" created="Tue, 15 Jul 2008 22:34:54 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;gah! .. must learn to read better.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12664586" author="pborgerm" created="Fri, 16 Jan 2009 17:59:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think runtime forceElevation should be possible (at least I stumbled on the need for it)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll attach a one-line patch here&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12664588" author="pborgerm" created="Fri, 16 Jan 2009 18:02:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;A one line patch, which defaults to the configuration value unless a query parameter forceEvaluation=(true|false) is given&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12664664" author="ryantxu" created="Fri, 16 Jan 2009 20:26:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks Paul.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I committed this with a slight change &amp;#8211; the patch you posted would change the forceElevation for any subsequent calls request.  This keeps the change with in the same request.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12664683" author="pborgerm" created="Fri, 16 Jan 2009 21:14:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks Ryan ! (blush) I did not spot the indeed obvious persistence through subsequent calls, nor was it revealed in my limited manual true/false testing series.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12664687" author="hossman" created="Fri, 16 Jan 2009 21:18:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;tweaking issue details to reflect realty (not a bug, no affects on 1.3)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12775514" author="gsingers" created="Tue, 10 Nov 2009 15:51:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Bulk close for Solr 1.4&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
